WHAT YOU MAY DO:
- Creatively design programme structures, propose new combinations of the organisation's components, and scale up delivery models — but ground everything in the organisation's real capabilities and cost structures.
- Programme costs should be realistic and derived from the provided cost-per-student figures, scaled appropriately for the proposed scope.",
  "user": "Organisation: TestOrg NPC

PIPELINE SNAPSHOT:
- Total grants: 6 (4 active, 1 won, 1 lost)
- Active pipeline value: R3,766,742
- Won value: R4,970,000
- Win rate: 50%

BY STAGE: Scouted: 1, Drafting: 2, Submitted: 1

FUNDER TYPES: Foundation: 3 grants (1W/0L, R7,006,000); Corporate CSI: 1 grants (0W/0L, R651,000); Government/SETA: 1 grants (0W/0L, R1,079,742); Tech Company: 1 grants (0W/1L, R300,000)

